body:
Version: Verilator 5.045 
The following SystemVerilog code causes an in the compilation step.
```
module verilator_error();
    logic clk = 0;
    bit q [$];
    logic [127:0] vec1;
    logic [127:0] vec2;
    always #5 clk = ~clk;
    always_ff @(posedge clk) begin
        q = {>>{vec1}};
        vec2 = {>>{q}};
    end
endmodule
```

The error when trying to compile
```
verilator_error___024root__0.cpp: In function ‘void verilator_error___024root___nba_sequent__TOP__0(verilator_error___024root*)’:
verilator_error___024root__0.cpp:80:41: error: no match for ‘operator=’ (operand types are ‘VlQueue<unsignedchar>’ and ‘VlWide<4>’)
   80 |     verilator_error__DOT__q = vlSelfRef.verilator_error__DOT__vec1;
      |                                         ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
```
From my research is that the streaming is not working correctly here. replacing the streaming operator with a for loop works but it is cumbersome on arbitrary and large streaming operations.

